default&#xa0;
defaultIntroducing the Women’s Engineering Society
default&#xa0;defaultThe Women’s Eng
defaultineering Society is a volunteer-le
defaultd, small charity in existence for over 90 years. Our members represent all sectors, are qualified in subjects from maths, 
defaultchemistry and biosciences through to PhD rocket scientists and all manner of engineering disciplines. They have entered technical professions through a variety of routes: engineering or science degrees, apprenticeships and even arts/humanities backgrounds.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe Women’s Engineering Society was founded in 1919 and has a history of working closely with government on issues relating to women and work with particular relevance to science, technology and engineering. The Society draws its members from a broad ran
defaultge of sectors including defence, manufacturing, sciences, banking and finance and all stages of education
default,
default and policy making. Members also reflect all career and life stages.
default&#xa0;
defaultOur submission 
defaultincludes
default exemplar cases
default drawn from personal perspectives and info
defaultrmation gathered from enquiries to our offices, recent surveys of members and a call for responses.
