default table 1); in the last 20 years the proportion of working engineers who are women has gone up from 6% to 8% - not a good return on all the effort. Something else is needed and WES believes it lies in workplace culture or “climate”. Measures that are long-t
defaulterm, 
defaultnot adhoc
default, should include support for:
